I can see that being a decent argument. although
{{item:3047}} {{item:3742}} {{item:3068}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3075}} {{item:3110}} will get you 1500 bonus HP and 380 bonus Armor;
reducing that by the easily attained "75%" will leave you with 95 armor. Costing 14,950g
While {{item:3111}} {{item:3065}} {{item:3102}} {{item:3190}} {{item:3156}} {{item:3512}} will get you 1200 bonus HP and 265 bonus MR;
reducing that by the "42%" will leave you with 150 MR. Costing 14,800g
So in the end you net more HP with armor and more resists with MR but with a more than likely bad build-path, not everyone wants to build {{item:3512}} {{item:3001}} {{item:3156}}
